HOUSE BILL No. 1243
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning local
government.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 36-9-37-14 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
2 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 14. (a) With respect
3 to a property owner who has secured the right to pay the property
4 owner's assessments in deferred installments by the filing of a waiver,
5 may, the municipal works board shall establish a policy to permit
6 an owner of real property in the municipality to prepay the
7 property owner's assessment in full by either of the following
8 methods:
9 (1) At any time after the expiration of the first year after the filing,
10 pay the entire balance of the assessment and be relieved of the
11 lien on the property owner's property. A property owner may not
12 pay the property owner's entire balance under this subsection
13 unless at the same time the property owner pays all interest due
14 at the next interest paying period.
15 (2) At any time, including within the year of the filing, pay the
16 entire balance of the assessment and be relieved of the lien on
17 the property owner's property. A property owner may not
